Carey,

I've come to the conclusion that investing in insurance and reinsurance
companies is a faith based investing. It is impossible to know if they wrote
insurance (and re) at good price points. It is tough to know what they are
exposed to. And it is tough to learn what they have invested the proceeds into.
Any of these parts of the chain can blow up into huge mess as we know from AIG
and you are seeing with ORI.

I faith invest in BRK and WSC. I tried to buy some SWCEY on Buffett's
investment that is now very under water. I am thinking of buying MKL and Y that
are often called mini-Berkshires, but I am not committed. A friend suggested
