From:E_K_S
Several of the Brazilian companies hedged their currency transactions with
$US/$Real future contracts and got caught with huge losses with the recent rise
in the $US.

ARACRUZ CELULOSE SA(NYSE: ARA) is one that hit a land mine. Their original loss
estimate was $500 million but after an internal audit their loss ballooned to
$1.7 Billion. Finally, they reported this today.

UPDATE 1-Aracruz unwinds derivatives at $2.13 bln loss
http://www.reuters.com/article/marketsNews/idINN0444177320081104?rpc=44

That loss represent $20/share. Yahoo reports book value at $18.00/share. Once
this loss is booked their new BV is negative! The company is discussing a
workout with their banks for a long term loan but this will double their
current debt load. The sad part about it is that the company is quite
profitable but now with this new debt load, it will impact their earnings many
years out as they pay down this new debt.

EKS
